Despite the brotherhood wars of the last years, the Iraqi society is relatively well organized, its leaders honor agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is characterized by the opposite symptom - no one can be trusted and no agreements are observed.
Under these conditions, the Afghan security forces are badly preparing, used to change the master every day according to how they are suitable.
Political institutions, even if formally established, will remain only a potemkin village, for which patriarchal tribal relations will continue to build.
Balancing the interests of different ethnic groups is extremely complex due to the unclear circumstances that make Pakistan and Iran’s influence even more complicated.
